{"id":14881187,"mediaExerciseId":"084dcfb3-1ca4-45fd-95fb-9968e6ff7980","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"9","chapterTitle":"Net Present Value and Other Investment Criteria","groupId":612332,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":305,"solutions":[{"id":5675549,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are to determine the payback period of the provided annual cash flow.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":60,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/22/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/cc897239ac8ae2af92e85b56fd2be4ff/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/22/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/cc897239ac8ae2af92e85b56fd2be4ff/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Payback Period**\n\nIt refers to the time required for an investment to recover the initial outlay of cost incurred.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/21/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/8b43dfd713342ed0d1dcaa07224528b5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/21/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/8b43dfd713342ed0d1dcaa07224528b5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The provided annual cash flow information is as follows:\n|  $\\hspace{0.8cm}$Year$\\hspace{0.8cm}$  | $\\hspace{0.4cm}$ Cash flow ($) $\\hspace{0.4cm}$  |\n|:------:|:---------------------:|\n| 0     | (8,300)  |\n| 1    |              2,100  |\n| 2    |              3,000  |\n| 3    |              2,300  |\n| 4    |              1,700  |","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/21/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/b5891efa407578659e04574b1679a59d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/21/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/b5891efa407578659e04574b1679a59d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"First, we need to compute the accumulated cash flow per year. It is calculated by adding the cash flow from the previous year to the current.\n\n| Year | Cash Flow ($)       | Accumulated cash ($)             |\n|:------:|:---------------------:|:----------------------------------:|\n| 0    | (8,300)  |(8,300)    |\n| 1    |              2,100  |(6,200)    |\n| 2    |              3,000  |(3,200)    |\n| 3    |              2,300  |(900)   |\n| 4    |              1,700  |                             800  |\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/18/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/06277774326772411bb47d0460f2ea60/lateximg_large.png","width":1410},"regular":{"height":92,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/18/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/06277774326772411bb47d0460f2ea60/lateximg.png","width":705}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"To calculate the precise payback period, we can use the following equation.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Payback period} &= \\text{YLNAC}+\\left(\\dfrac{\\text{AVLNAC}}{\\text{VFPACF}}\\right)\n\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\n $\\text{YLNAC}$ which represents the year of the last negative accumulated cash\n $\\text{AVLNAC}$ which indicates the absolute value of the last negative accumulated cash\n $\\text{VFPACF}$ which symbolized the value of the first resulting positive annual cash flow\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/13/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/5dbadbe2868ac6f7de8e92c9b48d2a4f/lateximg_large.png","width":1410},"regular":{"height":92,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/13/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/5dbadbe2868ac6f7de8e92c9b48d2a4f/lateximg.png","width":705}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Applying the formula of payback period:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Payback period} \n &=\\text{3 years}+\\left(\\dfrac{{\\$900}}{\\text{\\$1,700}}\\right)\n\\\\[10pt]\n &=\\text{3 years}+{0.53}\n\\\\[10pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{ 3.53 years}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nTo conclude, the payback period is **3.53 years.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":344,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/12/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/7ab69b6d1dffaac49544167d8db8a599/lateximg_large.png","width":748},"regular":{"height":173,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/12/c5c3c264ed8364a6efc26fb5afe74bcb/7ab69b6d1dffaac49544167d8db8a599/lateximg.png","width":373}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"f2a48d2a-430c-40f9-bd42-6fb44859ca91","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881189,"exerciseName":"3","page":305,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"dd43cc7c-cde1-4c0e-87d5-430018af3443","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-9-questions-and-problems-3-dd43cc7c-cde1-4c0e-87d5-430018af3443"},{"id":14881190,"exerciseName":"4","page":305,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3e3628e6-ceb1-45c4-8a4e-4176d408d9e2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-9-questions-and-problems-4-3e3628e6-ceb1-45c4-8a4e-4176d408d9e2"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881184,"exerciseName":"13","page":304,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9486733b-d942-4a5d-9e57-106d75d19507","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-9-questions-and-problems-13-9486733b-d942-4a5d-9e57-106d75d19507"},{"id":14881183,"exerciseName":"12","page":304,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b0e6f4ac-eeb1-4045-a513-9d032d5a52de","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-9-questions-and-problems-12-b0e6f4ac-eeb1-4045-a513-9d032d5a52de"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-9-questions-and-problems-1-084dcfb3-1ca4-45fd-95fb-9968e6ff7980"}